solution.p:
When t=0 we have W(0)=5 and H(0)=3 so that

   \left. \frac{dA}{dt} \right|_{0}
  &= \left.\frac{dW}{dt}\right|_{0} \cdot H(0) + W(0) \cdot \left.\frac{dH}{dt}\right|_{0}
   &= 0.3(3) + 5(0.2) = 1.9.

That is, at the beginning, the city is expanding at a rate of 1.9 \: \hbox{mi}^2/\hbox{yr}.
After 10 years, t=10, we have W(10)=8 and H(10)=5 so that

   \left. \frac{dA}{dt} \right|_{10}
  &= \left.\frac{dW}{dt}\right|_{10} \cdot H(10) + W(10) \cdot \left.\frac{dH}{dt}\right|_{10}
   &= 0.3(5) + 8(0.2) = 3.1.

At the end of the 10 years, the city is expanding at a rate of 3.1 \: \hbox{mi}^2/\hbox{yr}.

